        "title": "feat: add tool search directory mode",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add `tools.toolSearch.mode: \"directory\"` so large catalogs can expose a compact prompt directory plus `tool_describe`/`tool_call` controls while deferring most schemas.\n- Hydrate likely or requested directory tools from the catalog, including missing tool calls, while preserving sequential execution contracts.\n- Keep client tools directly visible in directory mode and document the new mode.\n\nFork attribution: based on JuanHuaXu/openclaw `codex/tool-search-directory-mode`, compared from `codex/fix-post-tool-continuation-guard`.\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json packages/agent-core/src/agent-loop.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs packages/agent-core/src/agent-loop.test.ts src/agents/tool-search.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.tool-search-run-plan.test.ts src/config/schema.test.ts -- --reporter=dot`\n- `git diff --check`\n- Merge-refresh proof at `796472c699`: `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json packages/agent-core/src/agent-loop.test.ts`\n- Merge-refresh proof at `796472c699`: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs packages/agent-core/src/agent-loop.test.ts src/agents/tool-search.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.tool-search-run-plan.test.ts src/config/schema.test.ts src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.test.ts src/agents/simple-completion-runtime.test.ts -- --reporter=dot`\n- Merge-refresh proof at `796472c699`: `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base upstream/main --codex-bin /Users/jason/.codex/openclaw-pr-autopilot/bin/codex-persist-sessions --model codex=gpt-5.5 --thinking codex=high` returned clean: no accepted/actionable findings.\n- Hosted Crabbox/Testbox live E2E: `tbx_01ktppx0dxxps5rf2qtzhg4jwy`, Actions run https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/actions/runs/27223948791\n\n- Deferred-replay fix at `1d8fca0082`: `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.test.ts packages/agent-core/src/agent-loop.test.ts`\n- Deferred-replay fix at `1d8fca0082`: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.test.ts packages/agent-core/src/agent-loop.test.ts src/agents/tool-search.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.tool-search-run-plan.test.ts src/config/schema.test.ts src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.test.ts src/agents/simple-completion-runtime.test.ts -- --reporter=dot`\n- Deferred-replay fix at `1d8fca0082`: `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD`\n- Deferred-replay fix at `1d8fca0082`: `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base upstream/main --codex-bin /Users/jason/.codex/openclaw-pr-autopilot/bin/codex-persist-sessions --model codex=gpt-5.5 --thinking codex=high` returned clean: no accepted/actionable findings.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- Behavior addressed: `tools.toolSearch.mode: \"directory\"` keeps authorized catalog schemas deferred while preserving normal validation, hooks, execution, result normalization, replay, and provider continuation. Exact head `55d9e5697968c0ec64d487eff32db59e284d32ef` also honors wildcard client-tool allowlists, keeps external tool descriptions out of the system prompt, converts deferred-resolver failures into paired tool errors, keeps client-owned names out of native capability guidance, and tracks the intentional config/plugin-SDK contract changes.\n- Real environment tested: Exact head `55d9e5697968c0ec64d487eff32db59e284d32ef` was tested from the isolated PR worktree against current `upstream/main` (`ded3a930587638d4014442db133e6d2cb40ab279`). The direct sibling Codex source contract was rechecked for deferred dynamic tools, tool-search response items, deferred spec planning, handler validation/search, and dynamic execution. The earlier hosted live Testbox proof remains feature-head-only: `tbx_01ktppx0dxxps5rf2qtzhg4jwy`, https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/actions/runs/27223948791.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.tool-search-run-plan.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.spawn-workspace.context-engine.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/system-prompt.test.ts src/agents/system-prompt.test.ts src/agents/tool-search.test.ts packages/agent-core/src/agent-loop.test.ts src/agents/tool-allowlist-guard.test.ts src/config/schema.test.ts src/agents/agent-tool-definition-adapter.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.tool-call-normalization.test.ts`; oxlint and oxfmt over all 23 changed TypeScript files; `pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check`; `pnpm config:docs:check`; `node scripts/pre-commit/pnpm-audit-prod.mjs --audit-level=high`; `git diff --check`; `git merge-tree --write-tree upstream/main HEAD`; `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base upstream/main --codex-bin /Users/jason/.codex/openclaw-pr-autopilot/bin/codex-persist-sessions --model codex=kepler-alpha --thinking codex=high`.\n- Evidence after fix:\n\n```text\nCurrent head: 55d9e5697968c0ec64d487eff32db59e284d32ef\nCurrent upstream/main: ded3a930587638d4014442db133e6d2cb40ab279\nFocused Vitest: 4 shards, 11 files, 447 tests passed\nAll changed TypeScript files: oxlint passed; oxfmt passed\nPlugin SDK API baseline: passed\nConfig docs baseline: passed\nProduction dependency audit at high severity: passed\ngit diff --check: passed\ngit merge-tree --write-tree upstream/main HEAD: passed\nPersisted Kepler autoreview: clean, no accepted/actionable findings\noverall: patch is correct (0.9)\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: Exact-head deterministic proof covers directory catalog construction, deferred exact-name hydration through the normal agent loop, wildcard client allowlists, dispatch/replay/capability boundaries, resolver-error continuation, external-description isolation, generated contract baselines, explicit-allowlist failure behavior, disabled-mode behavior, and current-main integration.\n- What was not tested: Exact-head hosted live directory lookup, deferred execution, and provider continuation were not rerun after these focused repairs. The prior hosted Testbox pass remains on an earlier feature head, and the previous exact-head Azure attempts were blocked before the model turn because the secret-backed hydrate provided no `OPENAI_API_KEY`. Protected operator/live channels were not used. Maintainers still need to decide whether the third persisted mode and generic `resolveDeferredTool` agent-core/session callback are the intended permanent compatibility boundary. No mobile, Desktop, or Telegram-visible behavior changed.",
